---
import BaseHead from "../components/BaseHead.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from "../consts";
import SpinningCube from "../components/SpinningCube.vue";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
		<style>
			.cube-container {
				width: 100%;
				height: 300px;
				margin: 2em 0;
				display: flex;
				justify-content: center;
				align-items: center;
			}

			.container-body {
				background-color: #3b3b5b;
				border: 1px solid #333;
				border-radius: 8px;
				padding: 0;
				margin: 20px auto;
			}

			.container-body b {
				display: block;
				background-color: #2a2a44;
				padding: 15px 20px;
				border-top-left-radius: 8px;
				border-top-right-radius: 8px;
				border-bottom: 1px solid #333;
				margin: 0;
			}

			.container-body ul {
				padding: 20px;
				margin: 0;
				text-align: left;
			}

			.header-container {
				display: flex;
				justify-content: space-between;
				align-items: center;
				margin-bottom: 35px;
				text-align: left;
			}

			.title-section {
				text-align: left;
			}

			.avatar-container {
				width: 100px;
				height: 100px;
				border-radius: 50%;
				overflow: hidden;
				border: 2px solid #333;
			}

			.avatar-container img {
				width: 100%;
				height: 100%;
				object-fit: cover;
			}

			main {
				text-align: justify;
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<div class="header-container">
				<div class="title-section">
					<h2>D3FALT</h2>
					<b>(Developer/Technical writer)</b>
				</div>
				<div class="avatar-container">
					<img
						src="/home_avatar.jpg"
						alt="Defalt Watch Dogs Avatar"
					/>
				</div>
			</div>

			<p>
				Hello World! This is my official devblog where I will talk about my developer journey.
				Documenting code, talking about my projects and their building process, lessons learnt and all the 
				braincells lost. 
				<br />
				<br>
				For starters, I am an English Major (+ econ minor) heavily interested in open source development and security, 
				technical writing, Research and analytics and Public speaking. My greatest programming aspiration is to contribute
				tangibly to the Open Source community, and perhaps build a somewhat successful SaaS startup that can help fund my expensive
				hobbies. 
				<br> 
				<br>
				<i>Maybe the real Google Summer of Code internship was the
					buggy code messes I built along the way.</i>
			</p>
			<div class="container-body">
				<b>My basic background:</b>
				<ul>
					<li>
						Currently pursuing an English Major, Delhi
						University
					</li>
					<li>20 years old based out of New Delhi, India</li>
					<li>
						Interested in open source development, Content writing,
						Documentation Engineering
					</li>
					<li>Proficiency in Python and Javascript Development</li>
					<li>
						strong expertise in research, prompt engineering,
						English proficiency, writing documentation, business
						communication
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<div class="container-body">
				<b>My projects:</b>
				<ul>
					<li>
						Debate Timekeeper project, built for the English
						Debating Society of my college
					</li>
					<li>This blog</li>
					<li>
						Debate Notetaking software - <a
							href="https://github.com/DefaltZ/debbynote"
							>Debbynote</a>
					</li>
					<li>
						<a
							href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1PzVwI4iFyFOajz5slKnfvp53aP5tVSsHXOXdPV5uXcs/edit?usp=sharing"
							>My Research/Writing portfolio</a>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<p>
				<b
					>Find my complete resume linked <a
						href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/11MnkSXYOEhb1LapHWaml4ptGzzubEnAi/view?usp=sharing"
						>here</a
					>!</b
				>
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
